The paper deals with non-cooperative game theory and the computation of Nash equilibria, which is a central topic in the field of computational game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses pure and correlated equilibria, which are related to algorithmic aspects of game theory (cs.DS). The use of algorithms to compute equilibria also falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the study of linear inequalities, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves mathematical proofs and analysis, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
